But since the rectangle only goes up to x=7, which is the point (7,0) and (7,1). So, this tiling works and covers the entire rectangle. Similarly, if we start with triangles going the other way, like (0,0), (1,0), (1,1), then (1,0), (2,0), (2,1), etc., up to (6,0), (7,0), (7,1). So, this is another tiling.
